==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unright
<hw>Un*right"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>unriht</ets>. See <er>Un-</er> not, and <er>Right</er>.]</ety>
<def>Not right; wrong.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unright</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unright
<hw>Un*right"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wrong.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor did I you never <qex>unright</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unright</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Unright
<hw>Un*right"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>right</ets>.]</ety> <def>To cause (something
right) to become wrong.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unrighteous</ent>⟦br⟧
